   "source": [
    "class Tweet(object):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, embed_str=None):\n",
    "        self.embed_str = embed_str\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _repr_html_(self):\n",
    "        return self.embed_str\n",
    "\n",
    "s = (\"\"\"\n",
    "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n",
    "Polyglot Data Science: Python, R, \n",
    "<a href=\"https://twitter.com/JuliaLanguage?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@JuliaLanguage</a> \n",
    "and Fortran cooperating in-process, through \n",
    "<a href=\"https://twitter.com/IPythonDev?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@IPythonDev</a>; \n",
    "demo code:\n",
    "<a href=\"https://t.co/93tIyWY68k\">https://t.co/93tIyWY68k</a>\n",
    "<br><br>\n",
    "Language wars among open tools are pointless, \n",
    "they complement each other.<br><br>Video/slides of the talk \n",
    "<a href=\"https://twitter.com/UCBIDS?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@UCBIDS</a>: \n",
    "<a href=\"https://t.co/voEKY5FUVj\">https://t.co/voEKY5FUVj</a>\n",
    "</p>&mdash; Fernando Perez (@fperez_org) \n",
    "<a href=\"https://twitter.com/fperez_org/status/987882327760977921?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">April 22, 2018</a>\n",
    "</blockquote> \n",
    "<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\">\n",
    "</script>\n",
    "\"\"\")"
   ]
  },
